      "content": "Of course. So, in that regard just kind of general practice for the most part is going to be to cover everything you had to tow with padded moving blankets and shrink wrap and then whenever it comes to your pictures and mirrors in particular more specifically pictures because they're a little bit lighter. We do also have the option of like using bubble wrap as well. Just to make sure that it doesn't get all you know, dusty and to provide an extra layer of protection in that regard. And then, once we prep it with those items we do have, depending on the size of the mirrors and pictures of course we do have a couple of options. The first one being Goos they are kinda like our large kind of gathering boxes, as it where they're about two foot wide. Four foot long and a a few foot tall to that end we use those to kind of create a case as it were to kind of keep anything from leaning up on them.",
